race.comment: Another tricky one. DIVINE CLEMENTINE (11) is coming off a tidy maiden win at Ballarat, scoring by half a length. She's open to further improvement and draws very well for Childs which could prove the difference. ART 'N' SOUL (6) was quickly up in trip last time when finishing behind STORM AHEAD who was a key chance before coming out in this race. He should strip much fitter for that effort and can prove harder to beat. REBADGE (2) did enough fresh on testing ground at Kyneton, beaten under three lengths. Better for that and while he doesn't win many, he sets up to run a good race. WEALDSTONE (8) is off a let up but will find this easier than racing subsequent G1 placegetter Zambardo last start in town. He can be running on late.
